metadata.name: Pride 9
metadata.description:
Pride 9 by Angele Etoundi Essamba, 2005

« Symbols » is a collection of 15 black and white portraits challenging the stereotypical representations of black women while promoting values of communion, equality and solidarity.

In this series, Angele Etoundi Essamba reflects on the identity of African women by highlighting the strength and the beauty of her models’ skin. 

Edition: 1/1
